    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A listing on the Oct. 19 cover describing ''What Does a Start-Up Need? Poetry'' said: ''Moses Ma, software executive, breaks up his employees' workday with poetry workshops. What rhymes with 'Java script'?''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>A listing on the Oct. 19 cover describing ''What Does a Start-Up Need? Poetry'' said: ''Moses Ma, software executive, breaks up his employees' workday with poetry workshops. What rhymes with 'Java script'?''</p>
        <p>How about this:</p>
        <p>Oh, who can describe, in a clear Java script,</p>
        <p>Volcano victims in a cold lava crypt?</p>
        <p>BEN KESSLER  Perth Amboy, N.J.</p>
      </block>
